The data used in this analysis consists of 51 months of power bills for a single customer. The first 29 months are from before the customer converted to solar power, and the last 22 months are from after converting to solar power. In figure \ref{fig:data} we can see that after converting to solar power, the customer had a lower power bill on average. One thing to note about these data is that they are correlated in time. Using a regular linear regression model in the presence of correlated data would still provide unbiased estimates, but we wouldn't be able to accurately quantify the uncertainty of those estimates. Consequently, we will use Gaussian process regression which allows us to specify a covariance structure that will account for the correlation in the data.

